<div id="pf1c" class="pf w2 h0" data-page-no="1c"><div class="pc pc1c w2 h0"><img class="bi x0 y0 w3 h1" alt="" src="bg1c.png"/><div class="t m0 x34 h2 yfb ff2d fs0 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">27</div><div class="t m11 x4a h26 y283 ff2e fs1e fc2 sc0 ls0 ws0">T<span class="_ _15"></span><span class="ff2f fs1f">h<span class="_ _11"></span>u<span class="_ _15"> </span>r<span class="_ _15"> </span>s<span class="_ _15"> </span>d<span class="_ _15"></span>a<span class="_ _15"></span>y</span></div><div class="t m12 x2d h20 y122 ff2d fs1a fc0 sc0 ls8 ws3e">July 18</div><div class="t m0 x23 h27 y123 ff32 fs20 fc0 sc0 lsa ws50">The Word: Revival’s Guardian and<span class="_ _19"></span> </div><div class="t m0 x23 h27 y3b8 ff32 fs20 fc0 sc0 lsa ws104">Safeguard<span class="_ _19"></span> </div><div class="t m0 x2b h5 y3b9 ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws88">The Holy Spirit mightily moved through the teaching and preaching </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3ba ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws52">of the apostle Paul as he established the Christian church in Ephesus. </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3bb ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws105">Ephesus was a city of approximately two hundred fifty thousand </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3bc ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws106">people. It was considered the marketplace of Asia. As ships brought </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3bd ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsfd">their wares from throughout Asia, people flocked to Ephesus to buy </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3be ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsae">fine silk, rare jewels, flavorful spices, hand-woven carpets, exquisite </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3bf ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsce">art objects, and exotic foods. It was also the center for the worship of </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3c0 ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws97">the goddess Diana and the future home of the famed Celsus Library, </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3c1 ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws65">with 12,000 volumes. The city had a magnificent amphitheater seat<span class="ws0">-</span></div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3c2 ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsea">ing 15,000 people. It was used for massive concerts and theatrical </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3c3 ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws96">productions. Sexual promiscuity was commonplace. If there ever was </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3c4 ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws50">an unlikely place for Christianity to take root, grow, and flourish—it </div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3c5 ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws1">was Ephesus.</div><div class="t m0 x2b h5 y3c6 ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m10 x3 h23 y3c7 ff31 fs0 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">Read</div><div class="t m0 x30 h24 y3c7 ff32 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsef"> Acts 20:27–32. What was Paul’s concern for the believers </div><div class="t m0 x23 h24 y3c8 ff32 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsb1">at Ephesus? What was his counsel to the church members in </div><div class="t m0 x23 h24 y3c9 ff32 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws1">Ephesus? What role did he give to the Word of God?</div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3ca ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">____________<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__<span class="_ _16"></span>__<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3cb ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">____________<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__<span class="_ _16"></span>__<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3cc ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">____________<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__<span class="_ _16"></span>__<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3cd ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">____________<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__<span class="_ _16"></span>__<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__________________________________</div><div class="t m10 x3 h23 y3ce ff31 fs0 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">Read</div><div class="t m0 x30 h24 y3ce ff32 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws57"> 1 Peter 1:22, 23; James 1:21, 22; 1 John 2:14. Summarize the </div><div class="t m0 x23 h24 y3cf ff32 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws36">teachings of Peter, James, and John regarding the importance of </div><div class="t m0 x23 h24 y3d0 ff32 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsa6">the Bible in the life of each Christian. Especially notice the dis<span class="ws0">-</span></div><div class="t m0 x23 h24 y3d1 ff32 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws1c">ciples’ teaching regarding the impact of the Bible in our spiritual </div><div class="t m0 x23 h24 y3d2 ff32 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lives.</div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3d3 ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">____________<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__<span class="_ _16"></span>__<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3d4 ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">____________<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__<span class="_ _16"></span>__<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3d5 ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">____________<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__<span class="_ _16"></span>__<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x23 h5 y3d6 ff30 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">____________<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__<span class="_ _16"></span>__<span class="_ _19"></span>___<span class="_ _19"></span>__________________________________</div><div class="t m0 x2e h24 y3d7 ff32 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws61">What similarities do you see in all of the above texts regarding </div><div class="t m0 x2e h24 y3d8 ff32 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws5d">the role of the Word of God? Why, then, must the Word of </div><div class="t m0 x2e h24 y3d9 ff32 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 wsd7">God be central to spiritual revival, both on a personal and on </div><div class=